            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_MYCtgW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Matching Necklaces With Different V-Neck Styles",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Matching Necklaces With Different V-Neck Styles</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_cx4fRn": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Matching_Necklaces_With_Different_V-Neck_Styles.png",
            "text": "<h3>A. Deep V-Neck</h3><p>A single long pendant, lariat necklace, or drop necklace enhances the vertical line of the neckline.<br/> If you prefer a subtle sparkle, a sleek piece like a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/rose-gold-diamond-necklace\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">rose gold diamond necklace</span></a> can add understated glamour.</p><h3>B. Wide V-Neck</h3><p>A shorter pendant necklace or a fine choker helps fill the empty space and draws attention toward your collarbones.<br/> For added sophistication, pair your chosen necklace with classic earrings such as <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond-studs\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">lab grown diamond studs</span></a><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">.</span></p><h3>C. Soft or Curved V-Neck</h3><p>Soft V-necks look best with necklaces that follow a gentle downward curve—think minimalist pendants or layered chains.<br/> This pairing works beautifully for both casual tops and elegant evening-wear.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "column",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "bezel-set-multi-shape-diamond-pendant",
              "1-13ct-marquise-pear-diamond-pendant"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6WCWXy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Styling Tips for V-Neck Outfits",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Styling Tips for V-Neck Outfits</h2><h3>1. Match the Metal to the Outfit’s Tone</h3><p>Cool colours pair well with white gold and platinum, while warm shades complement rose gold or yellow gold pieces.</p><h3>2. Keep the Balance Right</h3><p>If you're wearing a heavily embellished V-neck, choose a minimal necklace. For a simple neckline, you can experiment with bolder styles.</p><h3>3. Pair With Complementary Jewellery</h3><p>Your necklace should work harmoniously with other accessories.<br/> For modern styling, explore unique shapes through a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/modern-diamond-earrings-design\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">modern diamond earrings design</span></a> collection.</p><h3>4. Add a Touch of Shine With Bracelets</h3><p>When keeping your necklace simple, adding a bracelet can balance your entire look.<br/> A timeless choice is the <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/diamond-tennis-bracelet\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">diamond tennis bracelet</span></a>.</p>",
            "custom_id": "styling",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
